src/lib/data/drugs.json, src/lib/data/general_drugs.json
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: Examination and Payment Organization for Social Insurance /
支払基金 (Social Insurance Medical Fee Payment Fund, 診療報酬支払基金),
official 医薬品マスター (drug master) files published at ssk.or.jp.

Fields such as drug code, name, YJ code, price (薬価), and generic-name
classification are transcribed from this official master. Reference
document URLs embedded per record (documentUrl) point back to PMDA
(Pharmaceuticals and Medical Devices Agency, 医薬品医療機器総合機構),
pmda.go.jp.

This data changes on official revision schedules (通常年1回以上の薬価改定等).
It may be stale relative to the current official master at any given time.
Operators MUST re-verify against the current official source before using
it for real billing (レセプト) or dispensing decisions. The in-app
"設定 > マスタ更新" workflow re-imports the current official CSV/ZIP,
records a diff, and keeps a rollback file — use it rather than trusting
the bundled snapshot for production data.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
src/lib/data/drug_infos.json
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: Pharmaceuticals and Medical Devices Agency (PMDA, 医薬品医療機器
総合機構), official package inserts (添付文書) published at pmda.go.jp.

Every record's contraindications / interaction / usage-warning entries
carry a sourceUrl pointing to the specific PMDA package-insert page
(https://www.pmda.go.jp/PmdaSearch/iyakuDetail/...) the entry was
extracted from, and a fetchedAt timestamp recording when it was retrieved.
This dataset does NOT include and has never included content from
"くすりのしおり" (Kusuri-no-Shiori, published by the RAD-AR Council of
Japan / 一般社団法人くすりの適正使用協議会) or any other third-party
commercial reference. Only PMDA official package-insert text is used.

This is a point-in-time extraction and is provided for engineering/
operational reference only. It is NOT a substitute for consulting the
current official package insert. PMDA revises package inserts (改訂)
without notice to downstream consumers of this repository; the
contentSha256 field on each entry exists so operators can detect when
a re-fetch differs from what is bundled. Clinical and billing decisions
must be verified against the current official PMDA document, not this
snapshot. See docs for the official_drug_interaction_label refresh
tooling (`npm run drug-label:fetch`, `npm run drug-label:verify`).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
src/lib/data/receipt_remarks.ts
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
A short curated list of commonly used レセプト摘要欄記載コード (claim-remark
codes) used to populate the remark-selection UI. These codes are part of
the public 電子レセプト (UKE) record specification maintained by 支払基金,
but this file is a small hand-picked subset for UI convenience, not a
verbatim or complete transcription of the official code master. Verify
the current official code list before relying on any specific code here.

